SEC. 3.

Petition.

芒聙聰 The petition shall be in the form of an affidavit, subscribed and sworn to before any person authorized by law to administer oaths. It shall contain facts necessary to establish the merits of the petition and shall state the circumstances surrounding the abandonment or neglect of the child.

The petition shall be supported by the following documents:

Social Case Study Report made by the DSWD, local government unit, licensed or accredited child-caring or child-placing agency or institution charged with the custody of the child;

Proof that efforts were made to locate the parent(s) or any known relatives of the child. The following shall be considered sufficient:

Written certification from a local or national radio or television station that the case was aired on three (3) different occasions;

Publication in one (1) newspaper of general circulation;
